                <h1>Captivating Themes in The Yellow Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>"The Yellow Wallpaper" explores themes of mental health, gender roles, and the oppression of women in the 19th century. The narrator's descent into madness symbolizes the struggle for autonomy, while the wallpaper itself serves as a representation of societal constraints. The story reveals the dangers of isolation and the need for self-expression.</p>
